parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Unpredictable Throttle Response and Sudden Acceleration
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unpredictable throttle response and sudden acceleration can cause loss of control, accidents, and injuries to riders.
symptoms: The motorcycle hesitates or lags
then suddenly accelerates without warning
often when the fuel level is low (around 1/3 of a tank left)
on hills
or during turns. The low fuel indicator may not come on before the incident. The bike may stall
sputter
or jerk forward uncontrollably
making it difficult to maintain control.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The fuel system issues can cause the motorcycle to stall, hesitate, or suddenly accelerate, leading to loss of control and accidents.
symptoms: The motorcycle stalls or hesitates
especially when the fuel level is low
and may not display the low fuel indicator. The bike may require frequent refueling to avoid stalling or hesitation
reducing its range and making it unsafe to ride.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The clutch and transmission issues can cause the motorcycle to jerk, hesitate, or suddenly accelerate, leading to loss of control and accidents.
symptoms: The motorcycle experiences a "lag and leap" issue
where it stalls or hesitates
then suddenly accelerates
often when starting from a stop or making a turn at low speeds. The clutch may feel soft or spongy
and the transmission may slip or hesitate
making it difficult to maintain control.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel system can cause the motorcycle to stall, surge, or lose power, leading to accidents, loss of control, or injury to the rider.
symptoms: The motorcycle stalls or surges
loses power
or hesitates when accelerating from a stop
especially when the fuel level is around 1/3 to 1/2 full; the fuel light does not come on; the motorcycle violently thrusts the rider forward and then backward
potentially causing loss of control.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the output shaft can cause the motorcycle to lose power to the rear wheel, leading to a sudden loss of control and increased risk of accidents, especially when traveling at high speeds.
symptoms: The motorcycle loses power to the rear wheel
the throttle revs up the engine but does not propel the bike forward
the bike suddenly loses power while shifting gears
the bike is unable to complete gear shifts.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The faulty fuel pump can cause the motorcycle to suddenly lose power, leading to a loss of control and increased risk of accidents, especially when traveling at high speeds.
symptoms: The motorcycle suddenly loses power while driving
the throttle revs up the engine but does not propel the bike forward
the bike is unable to maintain speed.
